    "summary": "Expert on gender and women's human rights perspectives on cybersecurity with over a decade's experience in public administration, foreign policy, consultancy and intergovernmental and civil society organizations. \n\nKatya currently leads the \"Addressing the Gender Gap in the Cybersecurity Agenda 2022-2026\" project for the Organization of American States (OAS), providing technical support for gender mainstreaming in the design and implementation of regional cybersecurity policies. As an independent consultant, Katya also advises the OAS Inter-American Commission of Women (CIM) on the prevention of online gender-based violence, and Gender Associations International Consulting (GAIC), for whom she explores broader themes of the Women, Peace and Security Agenda. She has previously worked at the Mexican Ministry of Foreign Affairs, where she served as Director of International Women's Affairs, and at the Mexican National Commission to Prevent and Eradicate Violence against Women, where she was in charge of the first nationwide strategy to prevent online gender-based violence.\n\n- Advisory practice focusing on gender equality and international human rights law, gender perspectives of digital rights, gender and cybersecurity, WPS agenda, prevention of gender-based violence against women, advocacy and lobbying. \n- Technical support and advice on integrating gender-sensitive analysis and methodologies and implementing gender mainstreaming in the design, monitoring and evaluation of tech and cybersecurity policies.",
